### Banking Transactions API — sample requests
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension (or import into Postman).
### Start the server first:  npm run start:prod

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Create a deposit (funds arrive into ACC-12345)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "toAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "amount": 1000.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "deposit"
}

### 2. Create a transfer ACC-12345 -> ACC-67890
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "toAccount": "ACC-67890",
  "amount": 100.50,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "transfer"
}

### 3. Create a withdrawal from ACC-12345
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "ACC-12345",
  "amount": 75.25,
  "currency": "USD",
  "type": "withdrawal"
}

### 4. Validation error example (invalid amount, currency, account)
POST {{baseUrl}}/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromAccount": "BAD",
  "toAccount": "ACC-1",
  "amount": -5.999,
  "currency": "XX",
  "type": "transfer"
}

### 5. List all transactions
GET {{baseUrl}}/transactions

### 6. Filter by account
GET {{baseUrl}}/transactions?accountId=ACC-12345

### 7. Filter by type
GET {{baseUrl}}/transactions?type=transfer

### 8. Filter by date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/transactions?from=2024-01-01&to=2030-12-31

### 9. Combined filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/transactions?accountId=ACC-12345&type=deposit

### 10. Get a single transaction by id (replace with a real id)
GET {{baseUrl}}/transactions/REPLACE_WITH_ID

### 11. Account balance
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounts/ACC-12345/balance

### 12. Account summary (Task 4A)
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounts/ACC-12345/summary

### 13. Simple interest (Task 4B)
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounts/ACC-12345/interest?rate=0.05&days=30

### 14. CSV export (Task 4C)
GET {{baseUrl}}/transactions/export?format=csv
